==Mechanics==
The alchemist's amulet provides no benefit when making potions that always output 4 doses, including [[antidote+]], [[antidote++]], [[anti-venom+]], [[super combat potion]], and [[super antifire]]. The amulet will not trigger when creating [[Guthix rest]] tea; the player will always create a 3 dose cup.
<!-- The following potions need to be checked for effectiveness, and added to the table if it is: Magic essence, Sanfew serum -->

When used with potions that create a variable number of doses, the amulet will only trigger if the input potion is less than 4 doses. These potions include [[stamina potion]], [[forgotten brew]], [[extended antifire]], [[extended super antifire]], [[anti-venom]], [[extended anti-venom+]], and all of the [[Divine potion|divine potions]]. When used with 3-dose potions, the amulet will extend 60 doses into 63 doses, providing an average 5% increase in yield and taking 33% longer to make. For 2-dose potions, the amulet will extend 40 doses into 43 doses, providing an average 7.5% increase in yield and take 100% longer to make. For single dose potions, the amulet will extend 20 doses into 23 doses, providing an average 15% increase in yield and taking 300% longer to make. This takes much more time, but can be useful extending supplies when acquiring ingredients takes a significant amount of time (such as on [[Ironmen]] accounts, or maximising profit from [[crystal dust]]). Despite not being a potion, the amulet also affects [[Haemostatic dressing]], creating 4 'doses' instead of 3.

==Profit==
Since each [[amulet of chemistry]] adds ten charges, whereas the amulet of chemistry itself only has 5 charges, the cost per charge of using the Alchemist's amulet is effectively half that of the amulet of chemistry. When using the amulet for solely profit, it should only be used when a single dose of the potion you make has a value of more than 1/10th of the requisite amulet of chemistry's worth ({{NoCoins|{{#vardefineecho:amulet|{{GEP|Amulet of chemistry|0.1}}}}|c}}).

